Question16
Write a PHP function that takes two numbers as input and returns the sum of those
numbers. Display the result on the webpage, when a button is clicked.

ANSWER<?php
// PHP function to return the sum of two numbers
function sum($num1, $num2) {
    return $num1 + $num2;
}

$result = null;

// Check if the form is submitted
if ($_SERVER["REQUEST_METHOD"] == "POST") {
    // Get the values from the form input
    $num1 = isset($_POST['num1']) ? (float)$_POST['num1'] : 0;
    $num2 = isset($_POST['num2']) ? (float)$_POST['num2'] : 0;
    
    // Call the sum function and store the result
    $result = sum($num1, $num2);
}
?>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Sum of Two Numbers</title>
</head>
<body>

<h2>Sum Calculator</h2>

<!-- HTML form to take two numbers as input -->
<form method="POST" action="">
    <label for="num1">Enter the first number:</label>
    <input type="number" name="num1" required><br><br>
    
    <label for="num2">Enter the second number:</label>
    <input type="number" name="num2" required><br><br>
    
    <input type="submit" value="Calculate Sum">
</form>

<?php
// If result is not null, display the sum
if ($result !== null) {
    echo "<h3>The sum of $num1 and $num2 is: $result</h3>";
}
?>

</body>
</html>

OUTPUT
Enter the first number: 
100
Enter the second number: 
34
The sum of 100 and 34 is: 134

